dismissalText.long: c Shadman Islam b Nahid Rana
dismissalText.commentary: Yashasvi Jaiswal c Shadman Islam b Nahid Rana 56 (118b 9x4 0x6 205m) SR: 47.45

dismissalComment.html: Pace is pace, yaar. 148ks and Jaiswal fends to first slip, Wobble ball on a hard length from over the wicket. Angling away through the fourth-stump channel and Jaiswal tried to ride the bounce on the slightly open-faced defence. Ball took a thin edge and popped gently towards Shadman's chest. Cheeky smile and a wink from Nahid in celebration.

dismissalText.commentary: Mushfiqur Rahim c Rahul b Bumrah 8 (14b 2x4 0x6 21m) SR: 57.14

dismissalComment.html: another one bites the dust. Only a matter of time with the intense examination of skill and technique. Bumrah just keeps bashing the good length. Rahim plays the angle, and this ball does the rare thing: swing after bouncing. Remember Ryan Harris did that Cook. Rahim has the angle covered but that swing after pitching takes the outside edge. Rahul takes a sharp catch at second slip. Just too good from India. Watch this replay again and again, and marvel at the swing after bouncing. This usually happens to keepers after the ball has passed the stumps, but this time it has happened early and left Rahim no chance. Also a lovely catch from Rahul because the ball has swung away from him at the last moment. He moves with the ball, almost looking towards point by the time he completes the catch. watches it till the end, soft hands, and a superb reaction to the movement. Lovely cricket all around. A ball worth writing an essay about

dismissalComment.html: A superb catch by Rahul diving forward. He thinks he has caught it, the umpires have sent it upstairs to make sure. Huge cheers as Ashwin picks up his third, dismissing Mushfiqur for the fifth time in Test cricket

dismissalText.commentary: Shakib Al Hasan c Jaiswal b Ashwin 25 (56b 3x4 0x6 76m) SR: 44.64

dismissalComment.html: Bat-pad, Ashwin strikes in his first over of the day! This was what he was working towards yesterday as well, angle it in from around the wicket and use the bounce to his advantage. Shakib took a decent stride forward and tried to defend with a straight bat, which was close to pad. Ball hit high on the inside edge, brushed pad and went low to Jaiswal's left, he takes it with a nice little somersault. Smart field placement too as Jaiswal's was almost at backward short leg. 87.6ks but it looked slower to the eye. Lots of sidespin, lots of celebrations as Shakib's vigil ends
